Jan 22 '34
Dear Hiddy:
Mama sent on your letter about the fix you have been in, and I'm more soryr than I can say, I can't see how it happened, unless my first letter containing money and map reach you - or maybe it was the second. 
Anyway, I don't want it ot happen again! Surely there is no need of it, 
I've had a very fine trip. Will read here tonight & catch the 5:50 tain for Minneapolis tomorrow morning, then take the 9:20 train from there for Grinnell. Will reach home Thursday. 
(over) 
